# Comprehensive Crop Diseases Dataset

| Disease Name    | Affected Crops      | Symptoms                        | Treatments                             | Prevention Methods                       |
|------------------|--------------------|----------------------------------|-----------------------------------------|------------------------------------------|
| Powdery Mildew   | Grapes, Cucumbers  | White powdery fungus on leaves | Fungicides (Sulfur-based)              | Proper spacing, avoid overhead watering    |
| Blight           | Tomatoes, Potatoes  | Dark spots on leaves            | Copper fungicides, removal of infected plants | Crop rotation, resistant varieties         |
| Downy Mildew     | Lettuce, Onions    | Yellowing, wilting leaves       | Fungicides (mancozeb)                  | Good air circulation, resistant varieties   |
| Rust             | Wheat, Barley      | Orange or brown pustules        | Fungicides, resistant varieties          | Crop rotation, good drainage               |
| Fusarium Wilt    | Tomatoes, Peppers   | Yellowing, wilting of leaves    | Soil fumigation, resistant varieties     | Good sanitation, use healthy seeds        |
| Root Rot         | Various vegetables  | Wilting, blackened roots        | Fungicide treatments                     | Proper drainage, avoid overwatering        |
| Anthracnose      | Beans, Peppers     | Dark, sunken lesions on fruit   | Fungicides, removal of infected plants   | Crop rotation, use of resistant varieties  |
| Leaf Spot        | Cucumbers, Lettuce | Water-soaked spots              | Copper fungicides                       | Avoid overhead watering, proper spacing   |
| Sclerotinia      | Spinach, Lettuce   | Wilting, gray mold              | Removal of affected plants, fungicides   | Good air circulation, avoid overcrowding   |
| Viruses          | Various crops      | Stunted growth, mottled leaves  | No cure, remove infected plants          | Use virus-free seeds, insect control      |  

## Notes:
- Ensure all treatments are used according to manufacturer's instructions.
- Resistance can vary with different varieties; consult local agricultural extension services for best practices.